---

This month we had games with exploration, werewolves, and real estate - read on
for details!

!img realgatcha.png

First up Hirota Yukimasa presented Real Gatcha, a iOS game about exploring a
town looking for prize capsules. 

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rftUkLDb400
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rftUkLDb400?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


Next up, Aya & Marine of [Sympathy](http://sympathy.world/) presented Word
Wolf, a hidden role game for mobile platforms. The villagers all get a secret
clue, and have to use it to figure out who the wolf is before they get eaten!

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=ssX_lPCWnKo
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ssX_lPCWnKo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


Finally, [Gift10 Industry](https://gift10.co.jp/) showed their new game
[Madorica Real Estate](https://gift10industry.myshopify.com/pages/madorica_en).
A Switch game you play with paper printouts, you can work with friends to
cooperatively solve puzzles and exorcise real estate properties using magic
spells.

That was it for this month - catch you next time! ðŸŽ®
